frameDefinitions: These words refer to Parts merging to form a Whole.
One linguistic unit, Sign_1, has a relation to another linguistic unit, Sign_2.
Item-1 and Item-2 are compatible with each other if they can exist or function together in some context without problems, conflict, or other undesirable situation.
In this frame a Patient, which is  an organic substance, undergoes the natural process of decaying from an Initial_state to a Result.
This frame describes means actions (Preparatory_acts) that are taken by an Agent for the purpose of preparing for a later act.
This frame contains  words for Individuals as viewed in terms of their vocation.
frameExamples: The two droplets <t>merge</t>, and then travel down the windowpane even faster.
Make sure your site is <t>compatible</t> with any browser.
The leaves <t>rotted</t> into a mass of slime.
This update lays the <t>groundwork</t> for future improvements.
listRoleDefinitions: The entities that merge to form a single <fen>Whole</fen>.
The single, undifferentiated entity that is the result of the amalgamation.
The prominent entity that combines with <fen>Part_2</fen> to form a <fen>Whole</fen>.
The less focussed-upon entity that the <fen>Part_1</fen> merges with.
The time at which the <fen>Parts</fen> become amalgamated into a <fen>Whole</fen>
The location at which the amalgamation occurs.
FN: a linguistic unit that carries semantic, phonological or syntactic information.
FN: a linguistic unit
FN: Linguistic units
The Frame Element <fen>Item_1</fen> marks the grammatically more prominent of the two entities, i.e.the subject in active clauses, when they are expressed separately.
The Frame Element <fen>Item_2</fen> marks the grammatically less prominent of the <fen>Items</fen> when they are expressed separately.
This role is used when the <fen>Items</fen> are expressed jointly in a phrase, either a plural or a coordinated NP.
This Frame Element is used for expressions that indicate a <fen>Parameter</fen> or respect in which the <fen>Items</fen> are said to be compatible, not in conflict.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that undergoes a change.
The <fen>Time</fen> indicates when the rotting occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the rotting occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> uses the <fen>Preparatory_act</fen> to acheive a <fen>Purpose</fen>.
The action performed by the Agent that is a preliminary to the achievement of the <fen>Purpose</fen>. The <fen>Preparatory_act</fen> may also be expressed by a result of such an act.
The ultimate goal or purpose of the <fen>Agent</fen>, which the Preparatory_act enables.
The part of the larger process that is preliminary to the achievement of the <fen>Purpose</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Preparatory_act</fen> takes place.
The place where the <fen>Preparatory_act</fen> takes place.
The <fen>Person</fen> is the human being.
listRoleExamples: They had all just merged <fex>into one big file</fex>.
<fex>The single smaller soul</fex> merges with the Ur-soul.
The single smaller soul merges <fex>with the Ur-soul</fex>.
In one sense, <fex>dog</fex> is a hyponym of itself.
In one sense, dog is a hyponym of <fex>itself</fex>.
<fex>That technology</fex> turned out not to be compatible with the existing devices
My computer is not compatible <fex>with my new printer</fex>.
The two applications are compatible <fex>in their essential features</fex>.
<fex>The leaves</fex> rotted into a mass of slime.
<fex>Before he could get to the specimen</fex> , its entrails had decomposed so badly that they had to be thrown away.
Any traces of uneaten food will decompose <fex>in your tank</fex> and foul the water.
<fex>The company's actions at that stage</fex> were simply preliminary to the takeover.
We are still in the preliminary <fex>phases</fex>.
